reviews.reviewbody: One ROM I'm looking for is missing though, the latest version of Babel no Tou from the Namcot Collection.

@LongAccordian I didn't realize that this problem affected your other ROMs too. It's true that extracting the file makes it playable, but that payload issue should be reported to the developer of your ROM manager. Whatever compression features they use shouldn't trigger a warning from 7-Zip itself.

I personally use clrmamepro instead. Its UI is kind of cryptic the first time you use it, but it's a great program for verifying and trimming your sets.

------
my original comment:
There's some problem with your TwinBee (Japan) ROM. 7-Zip says "There are some data after the end of the payload data," and BizHawk can't load it.

Please replace it with the ROM from https://archive.org/download/no-intro-nintendo-nintendo-entertainment-system-20170618

Dragon Quest V is a Super Nintendo Entertainment System title.
You will need to check one of those sets for it.

Complete, reliable and organized! Good job! And thank you very much!

Regarding my previous post: it seems it is a matter regarding RA and its database, since it can't access the headers for these ROMs. But by doing a manual scan, it reads just fine.

The "Nintendo Campus Challenge 1991" ROM doesn't seem to be working.
What am I supposed to do to get it to work?
Just wanted to say thanks for the great work. as of 27/04 it is missing Mike Tyson's Intergalactic Power Punch (USA) (Beta). just wanted to let you know.
I don't know why uploaders feel the need to break conventions by uploading 7z files. Emulators don't read the format and converting them to ZIP is a huge hassle.

Instead of whining to the uploader, why not try a proper emu? .7z works just fine with mesen core in retroarch. 

Give yer balls a tug
Who actually cares about the file compression they use escpecially as its the rom file INSIDE the 7z what has the game on it. Betting everyones NES emulator can read *.nes files.
It's called "Kira Kira Star Night DX (Japan) (En) (Aftermarket) (Unl).7z", not "Kirakira Star Night DX (Japan) (En) (Aftermarket) (Unl).7z" :)
